What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Cardiovascular Genetic Testing Market?

Market Analysis and Size

The global cardiovascular genetic testing market is a significant component of the broader genetic testing industry and is focused on identifying genetic factors related to cardiovascular diseases. Cardiovascular genetic testing helps assess an individual's genetic predisposition to cardiovascular diseases, such as coronary artery disease, hypertension, and cardiomyopathies. This information can guide healthcare professionals in tailoring preventive strategies and treatments. Genetic testing can identify individuals at higher risk of developing cardiovascular diseases at an early stage. This allows for more timely interventions and lifestyle modifications to prevent or delay disease progression and due to all these factors, there will be an upsurge in the growth of the global cardiovascular genetic testing market.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global cardiovascular genetic testing market which was USD 7,336.36 million in 2022, expected to reach USD 17,152.16 million by 2030, and is expected to undergo a CAGR of 11.2% during the forecast period 2023-2030. “Inherited cardiomyopathies” dominates the disease segment of the global cardiovascular genetic testing market owing to the growing demand for better methods of bone related treatment. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include depth expert analysis, patient epidemiology, pipeline analysis, pricing analysis, and regulatory framework.

